The paper deals with graph-theoretical optimization problems and uses combinatorial and matroid theory concepts. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Among these categories, cs.DS and cs.CG are the most likely as the paper deals with graph algorithms and combinatorial optimization. The other categories are also relevant as they deal with discrete structures and computational complexity.
